ight also potentiate this interaction, i.e., dopamine D2 receptors could be not only more sensitive to dopamine but also to adenosine A2 receptor activation. Our results support this hypothesis, since membrane preparations from the denervated neostriatum are more sensitive to the effect of CGS 21680 on dopamine D2 receptors. Thus a low dose of CGS 21680 (3 nM), which is not effective in membrane preparations from the neostriatum of naive animals, is still effective in membranes from the denervated neostriatum. These results underline the potential antiparkinsonian activity of adenosine A2 antagonists. ?? 1992.},
